DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Pope Nicholas III

who   : A pope who sold the offices of the Church.
what  : A simoniac, planted head-down in stone with his soles on fire.
where : Circle VIII — Fraud, the third ditch (simony).
why   : He made merchandise of holy things.
when  : Head-down, waiting for the next damned pope to shove him deeper.
how   : He mistakes Dante for Boniface, come early to take his place.

class : Circle VIII · Fraud · the ten ditches of Malebolge
